Maintainer: Thiago de Paula Oliveira <thiago.paula.oliveira@alumni.usp.br>
Description: Provides comprehensive tools for estimating and analyzing longitudinal concordance correlation in repeated measures data. The package implements the variance components approach using polynomial mixed-effects regression models, allowing for robust estimation of longitudinal agreement. Key features include the calculation of concordance correlation coefficients, longitudinal Pearson correlation, and accuracy assessment over time. It also offers non-parametric bootstrap methods for confidence interval estimation, including the percentile method and normal approximation based on Fisher's Z-transformation. The methodology is based on Oliveira et al. (2018) <doi:10.1007/s13253-018-0321-1>.
